"{\"uid\": \"southernstar.ie-subscriber-exclusives-emily-hegarty-targets-one-final-push-in-olympic-b-final-4300974\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"August 1st, 2024 7:15 AM  ByKieran McCarthy  Share this article  EMILY Hegarty and the Irish women's four will look to round off their Olympic Games with a strong performance in the B final on Thursday morning (9.54am).\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 219, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 65, \"end\": 78, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Hegarty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"EMILY Hegarty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Hegarty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Hegarty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tokyo Olympic bronze medallist Emily had targeted a spot in the A final at these Games, but those dreams were dashed on Tuesday when the Irish boat finished in fourth place in the repechage - they needed to finish in the top two to progress to the A final.\", \"from\": 221, \"to\": 477, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 221, \"end\": 226, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_Station\", \"score\": 0.6569245140156686, \"rank\": 0.5217947525896499, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_Station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_Station\"}, {\"begin\": 252, \"end\": 257, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Dickinson\", \"score\": 0.9903147226516644, \"rank\": 0.009779933505733546, \"text\": \"Emily\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Dickinson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emily_Dickinson\"}, {\"begin\": 358, \"end\": 363, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9695785990972475, \"rank\": 0.0211213845715724, \"text\": \"Irish\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The four of Hegarty, Natalie Long, Eimear Lambe, and Imogen Magner found themselves in the repechage after finishing third in their heat on Sunday, behind The Netherlands and Romania.\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 662, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 634, \"end\": 649, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.884719679683297, \"rank\": 0.0525979453583857, \"text\": \"The Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 654, \"end\": 661, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9996291049352255, \"rank\": 0.0002566353243048175, \"text\": \"Romania\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Romania_national_rugby_union_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This meant Hegarty and Co needed to negotiate the tricky repechage to keep their medal hopes alive.\", \"from\": 663, \"to\": 762, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In second place after 500 metres, with just China in front of them, the Irish boat was right in the mix, but as China moved clear, the USA made their move.\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 923, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 812, \"end\": 817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9826081395130656, \"rank\": 0.015257938615348054, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 840, \"end\": 845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\